1
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:34,760
What are you doing?

2
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,120
Why are you yawning?

3
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:37,120
Fishing around again?

4
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:38,960
Fishing for what?

5
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:40,040
For shrimp!

6
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:41,200
No.

7
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,000
He's been fishing all day, doesn't know what to catch.

8
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:44,480
What's with the attitude?

9
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:47,120
Don't you know your own status?

10
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:48,280
Get to work.

11
00:00:49,480 --> 00:00:50,200
Wei Long.

12
00:00:50,720 --> 00:00:52,560
You really think you're the Princess's Consort?

13
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:53,560
Strategist.

14
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:55,200
If I really were the Princess's Consort...

15
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,560
I would have defected to the Kingdom of Dawei on day one.

16
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,560
The Lord might not even want you.

17
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:00,080
Strategist.

18
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:01,720
Say, if I really married...

19
00:01:01,720 --> 00:01:03,400
...the Third Princess of the Daye Kingdom...

20
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:05,000
...then would our Lord...

21
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,000
...give me an important position?

22
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:06,840
Stop dreaming.

23
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:07,960
Hurry up and work.

24
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:10,080
Working like this...

25
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:12,240
...my back is aching, this can't go on.

26
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,840
Strategist, think of something.

27
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:14,680
Don't ask me.

28
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:15,720
You're a great general.

29
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:17,120
And the popular Princess's Consort.

30
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,000
Figure it out yourself.

31
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:19,840
Yutong, don't get sunburnt.

32
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:31,280
Village Chief.

33
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:34,480
This is for you.

34
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:36,560
You have to help us with this favor.

35
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:38,000
Mobilize everyone.

36
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,320
What is this?

37
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:41,560
It's gold.

38
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:49,680
It's heavy.

39
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,520
Pure gold.

40
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,640
Works pretty well.

41
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:56,560
That's not how you use it.

42
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,680
Then use the other side?

43
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,120
No.

44
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:02,400
It's about the same.

45
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:03,840
V-V-Village Chief.

46
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:05,680
This is used to buy things.

47
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:06,840
Buy things?

48
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:08,840
For example...

49
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:10,000
If I...

50
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,320
...wanted your chicken.

51
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:12,120
Okay, okay.

52
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:12,880
Why didn't you say so earlier?

53
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:13,680
I'll give you one.

54
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,120
No.

55
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,240
I don't actually want your chicken.

56
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,000
You want eggs?

57
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,400
I don't want eggs either.

58
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:21,280
No.

59
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,400
Please sit, please sit.

60
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,240
V-Village Chief, it's like this.

61
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:26,800
Let's put it this way.

62
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:27,560
If you...

63
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:29,800
...wanted Da Qiang's duck.

64
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,400
...then you have to take this...

65
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,280
...and exchange it for Da Qiang's duck.

66
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:36,840
I understand.

67
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:39,000
Give this to Da Qiang.

68
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:39,440
Exactly.

69
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:40,400
Da Qiang's duck...

70
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:41,400
...becomes mine.

71
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:41,960
Yes.

72
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,440
Then Da Qiang uses this to crack walnuts.

73
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:48,160
Da Qiang wouldn't use it to crack walnuts either.

74
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,520
Then who cracks walnuts?

75
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:51,160
Why must it be about cracking walnuts?

76
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,000
Then what on earth is it for?

77
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:55,560
Village Chief, pretend I never came.

78
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,160
Your gold.

79
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,840
Keep it to crack walnuts and nourish your brain.

80
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:10,520
How did it go?

81
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:12,120
Didn't work out.

82
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,200
He doesn't recognize money.

83
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,520
It's not that he doesn't recognize money.

84
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,880
Did you teach them to recognize it?

85
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:16,960
I did.

86
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,000
And got a pile of walnut kernels out of it.

87
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:18,960
So getting the villagers...

88
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,760
...to help us catch shrimp is a bust?

89
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,000
I'm going to be worked to death later.

90
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:23,280
What can I do?

91
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,320
Taste this, it's quite fresh.

92
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,080
It's actually pretty tasty.

93
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:29,840
Brothers.

94
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,560
Don't rush.

95
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:32,200
Actually, I...

96
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:33,960
...can...

97
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,520
Let's first...

98
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,440
Strike first.

99
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:37,280
Good idea.

100
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,400
They are all quite harmonious.

101
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,880
We can't use force, okay?

102
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,200
No, I mean me and Xiao Hua.

103
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,000
Tie up Xiao Hua.

104
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,960
It won't cause much of a stir.

105
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,960
And it solves the problem.

106
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,520
Tie her up! Tie her up!

107
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:50,200
No, we need to tie...

108
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,400
...tie it very tight.

109
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,080
Come, look at the map.

110
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,400
Can you let me finish?

111
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,720
You shut up.

112
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:56,680
I...

113
00:03:57,080 --> 00:03:58,240
I have something to say.

114
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,160
Get out.

115
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:00,920
Fine.

116
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,360
I'm leaving. I'm going.

117
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:03,560
Don't regret it.

118
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,120
This is the Village Chief's house.

119
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,040
This is our place.

120
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:08,320
Where does Da Qiang live?

121
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:09,480
Over there, over there.

122
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,240
Later, the two of us will go over from here.

123
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:12,800
If we run into Da Qiang on the way...

124
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:13,920
Where's Da Qiang?

125
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,920
Strategist, did you eat Da Qiang?

126
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:17,560
Okay, okay, okay.

127
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,040
This...

128
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:18,800
This is Da Qiang.

129
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:20,160
Then pass by... Da Qiang is this one.

130
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:20,560
After going in...

131
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,480
Find Xiao Hua.

132
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:23,240
Did Xiao Hua go somewhere again?

133
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,800
Just put it there.

134
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:25,720
Put it right here.

135
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:27,120
Don't move. Stop moving. Okay, okay.

136
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,240
Eat a little less.

137
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:29,800
So annoying.

138
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,480
After going in, tie up Xiao Hua.

139
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:31,920
Forget it, forget it.

140
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:32,680
This is Da Qiang.

141
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,440
Hua is here. Xiao Hua is here.

142
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,680
We were just talking about tying you up.

143
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,240
Listen.

144
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,480
Right, we plan to...

145
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,600
Xiao Hua.

146
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:43,480
Qiao.

147
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,240
The efficiency this time is impressive.

148
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,560
Without the help of the two brothers...

149
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:48,720
...I got it done.

150
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:49,680
Get the rope.

151
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:50,800
What for?

152
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:51,880
What rope?

153
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,360
We have to find a place to hide her, right?

154
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,160
Yeah.

155
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,920
Do I need to hide?

156
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,040
I can hide behind the stairs.

157
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:58,680
Don't, Xiao Hua.

158
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,120
Brother is joking with you.

159
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:01,680
Anyway, hurry up.

160
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,600
Say hello to the two brothers properly.

161
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,040
From now on...

162
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:07,720
...we are family.

163
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,000
Qiao

164
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,040
Come here

165
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:21,480
What is it? I'm busy

166
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,160
Come here

167
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,120
What for?

168
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,480
How do you chase girls?

169
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,360
Why ask me this?

170
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:34,240
Fine, fine, fine

171
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,480
Since you asked so sincerely

172
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,120
then I'll tell you

173
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,800
It's actually very simple

174
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,560
Just two words

175
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:43,920
Be sincere

176
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:46,920
I'm pretty sincere

177
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:47,800
Hand

178
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,320
Like this

179
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:50,880
Make a fist

180
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,120
Masculine

181
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:54,880
Masculine

182
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:55,800
Masculine

183
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,160
Masculine

184
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,560
For you, also two words

185
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,240
Total compliance

186
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:01,480
What does that mean?

187
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,480
The meaning of total compliance is

188
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:05,360
no matter what she wants

189
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,320
you give it to her

190
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:07,240
no matter what she does

191
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,240
you do it with her

192
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:09,440
That is total compliance

193
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,800
But neither of these points is important

194
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,360
The most important thing is

195
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,240
good looks

196
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,680
As long as the guy is handsome

197
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:16,800
Where did they go?

198
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:23,480
Why did they leave?

199
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:25,480
Seriously, what kind of team is this?

200
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:27,000
Can't you do something proper?

201
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:40,160
Fighting is forbidden in the village

202
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,280
Stop pretending

203
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,160
The truth will come out

204
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,720
The truth between us came out long ago

205
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,320
But

206
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,280
no one believes it

207
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,520
What's the use?

208
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,480
Aren't you tired of pretending to be weak and innocent every day?

209
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,360
No, I'm not

210
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:55,920
As for you

211
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,480
pretending every day

212
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:59,200
to like someone you don't like

213
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,240
aren't you tired?

214
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,920
I lie for my country

215
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,520
I don't think I'm wrong

216
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:07,920
And you?

217
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,440
Lying to yourself

218
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,840
what is that for?

219
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:18,600
Put it away

220
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,200
Don't hurt yourself

221
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,240
By the way

222
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,560
I picked some flowers

223
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,520
If you like them, come get them from me

224
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:51,840
Wei Qiao's idea is pretty good

225
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:53,680
Being tough for a bit

226
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,880
actually worked

227
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,960
I need to try total compliance too

228
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:09,760
Miss Aqin, you're not asleep yet?

229
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,160
I'm sorry

230
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,960
I wasn't in a good mood yesterday

231
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,440
Being in a bad mood is right

232
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,280
No

233
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,000
What I mean is

234
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,560
when you're in a bad mood

235
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,880
you should find someone to fight

236
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,560
Didn't you tell me before

237
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,440
that you wanted to fight me?

238
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:24,000
Come on

239
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:29,000
Pretending to like someone you don't like every day

240
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:30,040
aren't you tired?

241
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:32,720
I'm not fighting

242
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:33,720
I didn't want to fight anyway

243
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:36,880
Miss Aqin

244
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:38,680
Are you worried you can't beat me?

245
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,160
I really don't want to fight

246
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:41,880
Then it must be

247
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:42,880
you're worried you can't beat me

248
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:43,760
How about this

249
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:45,840
I'll let you use a set of Qin Na

250
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,440
Come on
